{{Infobox given name | name = Andronika | image = | image_size = | pronunciation = | gender = Feminine | meaning = | region = Southeastern Europe | language = Albanian | origin = Greek | alternative spelling = | nickname = Donika | related names = | name day = | derived = | popularity = | footnotes = }}
'''Andronika''' is an Albanian feminine first name. It became popular amongst Albanians after Skanderbeg married [[Andronika Kastrioti|Andronika Arianiti]]. The name comes from Old Greek. The name means "victory of a man."<ref>{{cite web|title=Andronika - Meaning of Andronika|url=http://www.babynamespedia.com/meaning/Andronika|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref>
==References== {{Reflist}}
[[Category:Albanian language]] [[Category:Albanian traditions]] [[Category:Greek language]] [[Category:Names]] [[Category:Etymology]]

'''Antejuramentum''', and '''præjuramentum''', historically called '''''juramentum calumniæ''''' (literally, "oath to accuse falsely"), is an [[oath]] which both the accuser and accused were obliged to make before any [[Trial (law)|trial]] or [[purgation (law)|purgation]]. The accuser was to swear that he would prosecute the criminal, and the accused was to make oath on the very day that he was to undergo the [[Trial by ordeal|ordeal]], that he was innocent of the claims of which he was charged. If the accuser failed, the criminal was discharged. If the accused failed, he was intended to be guilty, and was not to be admitted to purge himself by the ordeal (see: [[combat]], [[duel]], etc.).

